Implements Pass A of the expansion pipeline: fans each `@count` entry out into one `ExpandedEntry` per count value from 0 to the bank's max (inclusive), merging bank-derived stroke keys into the last stroke chord and resolving `%d`/`%(EXPR)` and `%[ sep | body %]` repeats along the way. Entries lacking `@count` pass through untouched via `pass_through`. Type-slots (`%t`), body-breaks (`%b`), braces, and landings are deliberately left unresolved for later passes — this file only touches `Chunk::Dcount`, `Chunk::Computed`, and `Chunk::Repeat`.

The key semantic subtlety is the scope of `d`: outside any repeat it's the total count for that expansion; inside a repeat body it's the 0-based iteration index (`ITERATION_BASE`, currently 0 — changing this one constant changes iteration numbering dictionary-wide). `resolve` is recursive and threads `scope_d` and `total` separately so nested repeats and computed landings inside them see the right value. `resolve_computed` computes `a*d + b` in `i64` and rejects negative results with an error naming the offending value and `d`, never panicking or silently wrapping.

`uses_count` determines whether the template actually consumes a count (via `Repeat`, `Dcount`, or `Computed` chunks); this must be consistent with the entry's `@count` presence or `expand_counts`/`pass_through` returns a descriptive `ExpandError` — mismatches in either direction (operator without `@count`, or `@count` without operator) are treated as authoring errors, not silently ignored.

`fan_out` requires a non-empty `entry.stroke` (errors otherwise), splits off the last stroke segment, merges count-bank keys into it via `apply_count`, and rejoins with `/`. It depends on `crate::stroke::{apply_count, count_bank}` for the actual bank-key merging and count-spec parsing — those functions define what a valid `@count` spec looks like and this file doesn't duplicate that logic.

Public entry points: `expand_counts(entry: &Entry) -> Result<Vec<ExpandedEntry>, ExpandError>` (single entry, count-aware) and `expand_all(entries: &[Entry]) -> Result<Vec<ExpandedEntry>, ExpandError>` (whole dictionary, fails fast on the first bad entry). Both feed `ExpandedEntry` (defined in `super`/`expand/mod.rs`) into later passes that still expect unresolved `%t`/`%b`/braces/landings — downstream passes must not assume this pass fully resolves a template.